The Companies continue to recognize receivables for certain spent nuclear fuel-related costs that they believe are probable of recovery from the DOE. Dominion Energy&#8217;s receivables for spent nuclear fuel-related costs totaled $ 56 million and $ 52 million at December 31, 2022 and 2021 , respectively. Virginia Power&#8217;s receivables for spent nuclear fuel-related costs totaled $ 37 million and $ 39 million at December 31, 2022 and 2021, respectively. 

